Package: iCCL
Type: Package
Title: Objective PCA Dimensionality and Comparative Clustering for Seurat
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Arian", "Abbasi", email = "abbasi@hhu.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A small companion to the Seurat single-cell RNA-seq workflow. It
    replaces the subjective, eyeballed elbow plot with an objective, reproducible
    estimate of how many principal components to use for clustering
    (predictdimension), and then sweeps clustering across a range of dimensions
    and resolutions, saving one UMAP and/or t-SNE plot per combination so the
    biologically most sensible clustering can be chosen by comparison (iCCL).
